<casebody firstpage="1256" lastpage="1257" xmlns="http://nrs.harvard.edu/urn-3:HLS.Libr.US_Case_Law.Schema.Case_Body:v1">
<parties id="p-1">
  In the MATTER OF DISCIPLINE OF Lewis P. HANNAH, III
 </parties>
<docketnumber id="p-2">
  No. D-3059
 </docketnumber>
<court id="p-3">
  Supreme Court of the United States.
 </court>
<decisiondate id="p-4">
  February 24, 2020
 </decisiondate>
<opinion id="p-5">
  Lewis P. Hannah, III, of Philadelphia, Pennsylvania, is suspended from the practice of law in this Court, and a rule will issue, returnable within 40 days, requiring
  him to show cause why he should not be disbarred from the practice of law in this Court.
 </opinion>

</casebody>
